            margin: 20px;
        }
        h1, h2, h3 {
            color: #333;
        }
        code {
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 4px;
            padding: 2px 4px;
            font-family: "Courier New", Courier, monospace;
        }
        pre {
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 4px;
            padding: 10px;
            overflow-x: auto;
        }
        table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        table th, table td {
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding: 8px;
            text-align: left;
        }
        table th {
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Markdown Reference Guide</h1>

    <h2>Headers</h2>
    <p><code># Header 1</code> creates the largest header, and <code>## Header 2</code> is the second level, up to <code>###### Header 6</code>.</p>

    <h2>Emphasis</h2>
    <p><code>*italic*</code> or <code>_italic_</code> renders <em>italic</em> text.</p>
    <p><code>**bold**</code> or <code>__bold__</code> renders <strong>bold</strong> text.</p>
    <p><code>***bold and italic***</code> renders <strong><em>bold and italic</em></strong> text.</p>

    <h2>Lists</h2>
    <h3>Unordered Lists</h3>
    <pre><code>- Item 1
- Item 2
    - Sub-item 2.1</code></pre>
    <p>Renders as:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Item 1</li>
        <li>Item 2
            <ul>
                <li>Sub-item 2.1</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Ordered Lists</h3>
    <pre><code>1. First
2. Second</code></pre>
    <p>Renders as:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>First</li>
        <li>Second</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Links</h2>
    <pre><code>[Link Text](http://example.com)</code></pre>
    <p>Renders as: <a href="http://example.com">Link Text</a></p>

    <h2>Images</h2>
    <pre><code>![Alt Text](/images/example.jpg)</code></pre>
    <p>Displays an image with <code>Alt Text</code>:</p>
    <img src="/images/example.jpg" alt="Alt Text" style="max-width: 100%;">

    <h2>Blockquotes</h2>
    <pre><code>&gt; Blockquote</code></pre>
    <p>Renders as:</p>
    <blockquote>This is a blockquote.</blockquote>

    <h2>Code</h2>
    <h3>Inline Code</h3>
    <p><code>`code`</code> renders as <code>code</code>.</p>
    <h3>Code Blocks</h3>
    <pre><code>```
Code block
```</code></pre>
    <p>Renders as:</p>
    <pre>Code block</pre>

    <h2>Horizontal Lines</h2>
    <pre><code>---</code></pre>
    <p>Renders as:</p>
    <hr>

    <h2>Tables</h2>
    <pre><code>| Header 1 | Header 2 |
|----------|----------|
| Row 1    | Data     |
| Row 2    | Data     |</code></pre>
    <p>Renders as:</p>
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Header 1</th>
                <th>Header 2</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Row 1</td>
                <td>Data</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Row 2</td>
                <td>Data</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Strikethrough</h2>
    <pre><code>~~strikethrough~~</code></pre>
    <p>Renders as: <del>strikethrough</del></p>

    <h2>Task Lists</h2>
    <pre><code>- [ ] Task
- [x] Completed Task</code></pre>
    <p>Renders as:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Task</li>
        <li><input type="checkbox" disabled checked> Completed Task</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Escaping Characters</h2>
    <pre><code>\*literal asterisk\*</code></pre>
    <p>Renders as: *literal asterisk*</p>

    <h2>Footnotes</h2>
    <pre><code>This is a footnote reference[^1].
[^1]: This is the footnote.</code></pre>
    <p>Renders as:</p>
    <p>This is a footnote reference<sup>1</sup>.</p>
    <p><small>1. This is the footnote.</small></p>

    <h2>Syntax Highlighting</h2>
    <pre><code>```python
def hello_world():
    print("Hello, World!")
```</code></pre>
    <p>Renders as:</p>
    <pre><code>def hello_world():
    print("Hello, World!")</code></pre>
</body>
</html>
```

